"name":"Guillaume","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Germanic.  See  <b>William</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"William","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Guillaume de Chanteloup was born in 1245, in Chanteloup, Manche, Normandy, France as the son of Robert de Chanteloup. He had at least 1 son with Jeanne Neufbourg."},"et":{"1245–":"1245–Surnud","1245–Male":"1245–Surnud","1250–1290":"1250–1290","1265–1350":"1265–1350","1215–Male":"1215–Surnud","1215":"1215","1245":"1245","1265":"1265","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1290":"1290","Les Moutiers-Hubert, Calvados, Normandy, France":"Les Moutiers-Hubert, Calvados, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Chanteloup, Manche, Normandy, France":"Chanteloup, Manche, Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1245–":"1245–Kuollut","1245–Male":"1245–Kuollut","1250–1290":"1250–1290","1265–1350":"1265–1350","1215–Male":"1215–Kuollut","1215":"1215","1245":"1245","1265":"1265","1350":"1350","1250":"1250","1290":"1290","Les Moutiers-Hubert, Calvados, Normandy, France":"Les Moutiers-Hubert, Calvados, Normandie, Ranska","Chanteloup, Manche, Normandy, France":"Chanteloup, Manche, Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1245–":"1245–Décédé","1245–Male":"1245–Décédé","1250–1290":"1250–1290","1265–1350":"1265–1350","1215–Male":"1215–Décédé","1215":"1215","1245":"1245","1265":"1265","1350":"1350